    {
        "content": "<p>Hmm, perhaps the issue is that the <code>if</code>-<code>then</code>-<code>else</code> may mutate <code>i</code> (before <code>__do_jp</code>), and so we would no longer have an <code>h</code> to pass along. So I suppose the question is: is it also too costly to detect mutation of <code>i</code> within <code>if</code>-<code>then</code>-<code>else</code>?</p>",
